main event: A ground-radar target was observed, and a silvery, oval-shaped object was seen passing overhead at a high rate of speed with a pulsing light.
interesting points: The object swerved to the southeast and accelerated to a tremendous speed after passing overhead.
What appeared to be grey or silver flashes were observed.
The total sighting lasted for about 20 seconds.
The weather conditions were clear with high winds up to 30 knots at high altitudes.
Weather balloons released in the area could not account for the sighting.
